    "Data access frameworks with democratic oversight and mandatory sharing for qualifying purposes could be impactful, but little has been achieved through the updated Code of Practice on Disinformation [2,49].",
    "Technical solutions granting access could involve requiring availability through open APIs of privacy-preserving synthetic platform datasets, development of trusted intermediary data institutions to broker access, and heightening researcher intimacy levels to unlock voluntary sharing.",
    "ConclusionThis paper aimed to catalyze scholarly discourse on empirically evaluating the DSA's efficacy in achieving its central goal of combating online harms.",
    "It provided necessary context on the DSA's mechanisms and expected effects to situate the analysis.",
    "An extensive multi-disciplinary critique then surfaced meaningful gaps requiring ongoing regulatory and evidentiary oversight."
